    <div id="content" tabindex="0" class="container"> 
     <h1 class="text-center">Cybersecurity research at Stanford</h1> 
     <div class="row"> 
      <div class="col-md-10 col-md-offset-1"> 
       <p id="sharethis"> <span class="st_fblike_hcount"></span> <span class="st_facebook_hcount" displaytext="Facebook"></span> <span class="st_twitter_hcount" displaytext="Tweet"></span> <span class="st_email_hcount" displaytext="Email"></span> </p> 
      </div> 
      <div class="col-md-10 col-md-offset-1"> 
       <p class="lead">In a world increasingly dependent on modern technology, cybersecurity is one of humanity's most pressing issues. Stanford's broad network of thought leaders are taking an interdisciplinary approach to tackling the range of challenges and opportunities created by ever-changing technical advances. Here are just a few examples of how Stanford is working to address the world's cybersecurity challenges.</p> 
      </div> 
     </div> 
     <div class="row"> 
      <div id="content-section-1" class="row content-section"> 
       <div class="col-md-5 col-md-offset-1 well"> 
        <h3 style="font-size: 1.5em; text-align:center">The Stanford Cyber Initiative</h3> 
        <p style="text-align:center; padding-top: 20px;"><span class="icon"><i class="fa fa-3x fa-lock"></i></span></p> 
        <p>Stanford’s university-wide initiative to understand cyberspace, cybersecurity, and the challenges and opportunities that networked information pose to humanity. The initiative is supported by a $15 million grant from the William and Flora Hewlett Foundation.</p> 
        <p class="more-link" style="display:block; text-align: right"> <a data-ua-label="external-link" data-ua-action="cyber.stanford.edu" data-caption="" href="http://cyber.stanford.edu"><i class="fa fa-chevron-circle-right"></i> <span>Learn more</span></a> </p> 
       </div> 
       <div class="col-md-5 well spacing"> 
        <h3 style="font-size: 1.5em; text-align:center">White House Cybersecurity Summit</h3> 
        <p style="text-align:center; padding-top: 20px;"><span class="icon whitehouse"><i class="fa fa-3x fa-university"></i></span></p> 
        <p>On February 13, 2015, the White House hosted a <em>Summit on Cybersecurity and Consumer Protection</em> at Stanford. The summit convened major stakeholders to help shape public and private sector efforts to protect consumers and companies from growing network threats.</p> 
        <p class="more-link" style="display:block; text-align: right"> <a data-ua-label="external-link" data-ua-action="cyber.stanford.edu" data-caption="" href="http://news.stanford.edu/tags/cybersecurity/"><i class="fa fa-chevron-circle-right"></i> <span>Learn more</span></a> </p> 
       </div> 
      </div> 
     </div> 
    </div> 
    <div class="container-fluid people-list" style="background-color:#f2f1eb; margin:20px 0 0 0; padding:20px 0 0 0"> 
     <div class="container"> 
      <div class="row"> 
       <div class="col-md-10 col-md-offset-1"> 
        <h2 class="text-center"><i class="fa fa-user" style="color: #c7d1c5;"></i>Stanford experts on cybersecurity</h2> 
        <p class="text-center"> Stanford researchers in fields related to cybersecurity include:</p> 
        <div class="row"> 
         <div class="col-sm-3"> 
          <h4>Herb Lin</h4> 
          <ul> 
           <li><a href="http://cisac.fsi.stanford.edu/people/herbert_lin">senior research scholar</a> at CISAC for cyber policy and security</li> 
           <li><a href="http://www.hoover.org/profiles/herbert-lin">research fellow</a> at the Hoover Institution</li> 
          </ul> 
         </div> 
         <div class="col-sm-3"> 
          <h4>Jonathan Mayer</h4> 
          <ul> 
           <li><a href="http://cyberlaw.stanford.edu/about/people/jonathan-mayer">cybersecurity fellow</a> at CISAC</li> 
           <li>research fellow at the Law School's Center for Internet and Society</li> 
          </ul> 
         </div> 
         <div class="col-sm-3"> 
          <h4>Tim Junio</h4> 
          <ul> 
           <li><a href="http://fsi.stanford.edu/people/timothy_junio">cybersecurity research affiliate</a> at CISAC</li> 
           <li>cybersecurity fellow at the Hoover Institution</li> 
          </ul> 
         </div> 
         <div class="col-sm-3"> 
          <h4>Michael McFaul</h4> 
          <ul> 
           <li><a href="http://fsi.stanford.edu/people/michael_a_mcfaul">professor</a> of political science, director of Freeman Spogli Institute for International Studies</li> 
           <li><a href="http://www.hoover.org/profiles/michael-mcfaul">senior fellow</a> at the Hoover Institution</li> 
          </ul> 
         </div> 
        </div> 
        <div class="row"> 
         <div class="col-sm-3 "> 
          <h4>Barbara Van Schewick</h4> 
          <ul> 
           <li><a href="http://cyberlaw.stanford.edu/about/people/barbara-van-schewick">director</a> of Stanford Law School’s <a href="http://cyberlaw.stanford.edu/">Center for Internet and Society</a></li> 
          </ul> 
         </div> 
         <div class="col-sm-3"> 
          <h4>Jennifer Granick</h4> 
          <ul> 
           <li><a href="http://cyberlaw.stanford.edu/about/people/jennifer-granick">director</a> of civil liberties at the Stanford Center for Internet and Society</li> 
          </ul> 
         </div> 
         <div class="col-sm-3"> 
          <h4>Amy Zegart</h4> 
          <ul> 
           <li><a href="http://fsi.stanford.edu/people/amy_zegart">co-director</a> at CISAC</li> 
           <li><a href="http://www.hoover.org/profiles/amy-zegart">senior fellow</a> at the Hoover Institution</li> 
          </ul> 
         </div> 
         <div class="col-sm-3"> 
          <h4>Dan Boneh</h4> 
          <ul> 
           <li><a href="https://profiles.stanford.edu/dan-boneh?tab=bio">professor</a> of computer science</li> 
           <li>co-director of Stanford Computer Security Lab</li> 
          </ul> 
         </div> 
        </div> 
        <div class="row"> 
         <div class="col-sm-3"> 
          <h4>Abraham Sofaer</h4> 
          <ul> 
           <li><a href="http://www.hoover.org/profiles/abraham-d-sofaer">distinguished scholar and senior fellow</a> at the Hoover Institution</li> 
          </ul> 
         </div> 
        </div> 
       </div> 
      </div> 
     </div> 
    </div> 
